  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev22 changes:
    - MainActivity.java: onDestroy() now calls _flushReviewEvalCache() (via
      webView.evaluateJavascript) and stockfishEngine.persistentFlush() BEFORE
      calling _cleanupEventListeners() and stockfishEngine.shutdown(). This
      ensures any eval data that arrived between onStop and onDestroy (e.g.,
      during low-memory kill where onStop may be skipped) is flushed to disk
      before the WebView is destroyed.

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev23 changes:
    - StockfishNative.java: saveEvalCacheSync() now uses Files.move() with
      ATOMIC_MOVE + REPLACE_EXISTING on API 26+ for true POSIX-atomic rename.
      The old delete+renameTo sequence had a brief window where neither old
      nor new file existed (app crash in that window = cache lost). API 21-25
      retains the legacy path (renameTo is still POSIX-atomic on same FS, but
      Java's renameTo doesn't overwrite — hence the delete).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev24 changes:
    - No changes to Java sources in this revision. All Rev24 changes are in
      the JS layer (chess.src/) and the Stockfish engine binary
      (src/main/jniLibs/arm64-v8a/libstockfish.so, updated to the official
      sf_18 arm64-v8a-dotprod release, 114 MB, NDK r27c build).
    - The existing Java-side persistent storage APIs (persistentGet/Set/
      Remove/SetSync/Flush, saveEvalCacheSync/loadEvalCacheSync,
      savePGNCache/getPGNCache/listPGNCaches/deletePGNCaches/renamePGNCache/
      setPGNCacheTags/getPGNCacheTags) are reused as-is by the new JS
      features (player rename, PGN-comment eval extraction, analyze-all
      resilience). No new @JavascriptInterface methods were needed.

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev25 changes:
    - No changes to Java sources. All Rev25 changes are in the JS layer
      (chess.src/ui.js — Chess960 dialog heading removal) and stats.html
      (promotion symbol rendering fix).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev26 changes:
    - No changes to Java sources. The Rev26 fix is entirely in stats.html
      (SAN regex alternative for non-capture pawn promotions).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev27 changes:
    - StockfishNative.java (Rev27, GPL v3): added new @JavascriptInterface
      method openUrlInBrowser(String url). Launches the system default
      browser via Intent.ACTION_VIEW with FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK. URLs are
      strictly validated to be http(s) only — file:, content:, javascript:,
      intent: schemes are silently rejected (defense against intent-scheme
      injection). Called from JS when the user taps any hyperlink in the
      About dialog or anywhere in chess.html.
    - ChessWebViewClient.java (Rev27, AGPL v3): shouldOverrideUrlLoading()
      now OPENS external http(s) URLs in the system default browser instead
      of silently blocking them. This is defense-in-depth alongside the
      JS-side openUrlInBrowser bridge — if a link is triggered by other
      means (meta refresh, JS window.open), this WebViewClient layer
      catches it. URLs are validated to be http(s); all other schemes are
      blocked.
    - StatsActivity.java (Rev27, AGPL v3): added new @JavascriptInterface
      method openUrlInBrowser(String url) to the inline JS bridge object —
      same security model as StockfishNative.openUrlInBrowser (http(s)
      only). Also updated the WebViewClient's shouldOverrideUrlLoading to
      open http(s) URLs in the system browser (matching the main WebView's
      behavior).
    - No changes to other Java sources (MainActivity, ChessApp, EngineService,
      RootDetector, TlsSecurityHelper). All other Rev27 changes are in the
      JS layer (chess.src/ui.js, chess.src/ai-bridge.js, chess.src/game-logic.js
      — resign feature, hyperlink click handler, About page GitHub link,
      i18n keys) and stats.html (Backspace fix, applySANMove king-safety,
      _escFEN escaping, exportFullHTML regex, board display, hyperlink
      click handler, i18n key for board section heading).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev28 changes:
    - StatsActivity.java (Rev28, AGPL v3): added new static volatile field
      `importedPGNOnStats` (String) — stashes the PGN text imported on the
      stats page for MainActivity.onResume to read. Added new
      @JavascriptInterface method `setImportedPGN(String pgnText)` that
      sets the field. Updated `onKeyDown(KEYCODE_BACK)` to delegate to the
      JS-side returnToGame() (via evaluateJavascript) so the import-back
      interceptor can fire; if the import-back dialog is visible, back =
      Cancel (dismiss dialog).
    - MainActivity.java (Rev28, AGPL v3): onResume() now checks
      StatsActivity.importedPGNOnStats; if non-null, reads it, clears it
      (one-shot consumption), JSON-encodes it, and calls the JS-side
      `_showStatsImportBackPrompt(pgn)` function via evaluateJavascript.
      The JSON encoding uses org.json.JSONObject for safe JS string passing.
    - No changes to other Java sources (StockfishNative, ChessApp,
      ChessWebViewClient, EngineService, RootDetector, TlsSecurityHelper).
      All other Rev28 changes are in the JS layer (chess.src/ui.js —
      _showStatsImportBackPrompt; chess.src/ai-bridge.js — openStatsPage
      always rebuilds from moveRecords; chess.src/game-logic.js — i18n
      keys; chess.src/tablebase.js — promotion field in moveRecords.push;
      ui.js game-over emoji fix) and stats.html (import-back dialog,
      _statsImportedPGN tracking, returnToGame/requestReview interception).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev29 changes:
